columns.label: Construct Coverage raw
columns.description: Protein Precedence component: experimental construct coverage. It is the coverage fraction of the region by the TAPIR construct that maximizes coverage. Numeric, possible values: [0..1]

columns.label: Construct Coverage
columns.description: Protein Precedence component: experimental construct coverage. It is the coverage fraction of the region by the TAPIR construct that maximizes coverage. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: Construct Expression raw
columns.description: Protein Precedence component: protein expression yield. It scores expression concentration (in mg/mL) of the TAPIR construct that maximizes coverage. 0 if expression concentration is <= 0.1 mg/ml, 2 if it is 0.1-0.5 mg/ml, 3 if it is 0.5-1.0 mg/ml and 4 if it is > 1.0 mg/ml. Integer, possible values: [0..4].

columns.label: Construct Expression

Integer, possible values: [0..10].

columns.label: Experimental Protein raw
columns.description: Protein Precedence component: good experimental structures. It scores 5 x identity [0..1] x coverage [0..1] if the structure with the largest coverage has % identity >= 95%; otherwise 0. Numeric, possible values: [0..5]

columns.label: Experimental Protein
columns.description: Protein Precedence component: good experimental structures. It scores 5 x identity [0..1] x coverage [0..1] if the structure with the largest coverage has % identity >= 95%; otherwise 0. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: PROTEIN PRECEDENCE Raw
columns.description: Construct analysis and experimental structure precedence score. Sum of all three components of protein precedence: Construct Coverage, Construct Expression, and Experimental Protein Precedence. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: PROTEIN PRECEDENCE
columns.description: Construct analysis and experimental structure precedence score. Sum of all three components of protein precedence: Construct Coverage, Construct Expression, and Experimental Protein Precedence. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: Structure Coverage raw
columns.description: Experimental Structure Precedence component: How well the experimental structure sequence covers the UniProt sequence. Maximum coverage fraction of the structure against the reference (UniProt sequence, region). For a score > 0 it requires at least 5 residues of coverage. Numeric, possible values: [0..1]

columns.label: Structure Coverage
columns.description: Experimental Structure Precedence component: How well the experimental structure sequence covers the UniProt sequence. Maximum coverage fraction of the structure against the reference (UniProt sequence, region). For a score > 0 it requires at least 5 residues of coverage. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: Structure Resolution raw
columns.description: Experimental Structure Precedence component: The highest resolution experimental structure available. Score based on the atomic resolution (A) of the structure with the largest coverage. A value of 0 implies no structure. Otherwise, 0.2 if resolution is greater than 4 A, 0.4 if resolution is 3-4 A, 0.7 if resolution is 2.4-3.0 A, 0.9 if resolution is 1.8-2.4 A, and 1.0 if resolution is less than 1.8 A. Float, possible values: [0..1]

columns.label: Structure Resolution
columns.description: Experimental Structure Precedence component: The highest resolution experimental structure available. Score based on the atomic resolution (A) of the structure with the largest coverage. A value of 0 implies no structure. Otherwise, 0.2 if resolution is greater than 4 A, 0.4 if resolution is 3-4 A, 0.7 if resolution is 2.4-3.0 A, 0.9 if resolution is 1.8-2.4 A, and 1.0 if resolution is less than 1.8 A. Float, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: Structure Identity Raw
columns.description: Experimental Structure Precedence component: How much the available experimental structures have similarity against the UniProt sequence. Score based on the % identity of the structure with the largest coverage against the reference (UniProt). The score is assigned based on a range of percent identity (in fractional form), where 0 means no structure, otherwise 0.05 if % ident. <= 70%, 0.7 if % ident. is 70-85%, 0.9 if % ident. is 85-98%, and 1.0 if % ident. is 98-100%. Float, possible values: [0..1]

columns.label: Structure Identity
columns.description: Experimental Structure Precedence component: How much the available experimental structures have similarity against the UniProt sequence. Score based on the % identity of the structure with the largest coverage against the reference (UniProt). The score is assigned based on a range of percent identity (in fractional form), where 0 means no structure, otherwise 0.05 if % ident. <= 70%, 0.7 if % ident. is 70-85%, 0.9 if % ident. is 85-98%, and 1.0 if % ident. is 98-100%. Float, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: Number of Structures raw
columns.description: Experimental Structure Precedence component: Number of available experimental structures. Score based on the number of available experimental structures, where 0 means no structure, otherwise 0.7 if 1-3 structures are available, 0.85 if 3-8 structures are available, 1.0 if >=8 structures are available. Float, possible values: [0..1]

columns.label: Number of Structures
columns.description: Experimental Structure Precedence component: Number of available experimental structures. Score based on the number of available experimental structures, where 0 means no structure, otherwise 0.7 if 1-3 structures are available, 0.85 if 3-8 structures are available, 1.0 if >=8 structures are available. Float, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: Exp Structure
columns.description: 10 X Multiple of experimental structure coverage, resolution, identity, number of structures scores. Product of all experimental structure precedence components [0..1] scaled to 10 [0..10]. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: AF2 Model
columns.description: Overall Structure Precedence component: Coverage and confidence of AlphaFold model. Score based on average amino acids with pDDLT values higher or equal to 70% scaled by the coverage fraction of kept residues in a region. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: STRUCTURE PRECEDENCE
columns.description: Structure precedence calculated from experimental structure or AlphaFold structure precedence. This score is composed of 75% of the Experimental Structure Precedence score and 25% of the AlphaFold Structure score. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: TRACTABILITY Raw
columns.description: Overall Protein Precedence and Overall Structure Precedence combined score. Sum of Overall Protein Precedence and Overall Structure Precedence scores. Numeric, possible values: [0..20]

columns.label: TRACTABILITY
columns.description: Overall Protein Precedence and Overall Structure Precedence combined score. Sum of Overall Protein Precedence and Overall Structure Precedence scores on 10 points scale. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: Exp LIG Raw
columns.description: Pocket Precedence component: Experimental ligand that satisfies rule-of-five. Score is 6 if the PDB ligands satisfy Lipinski's rule of five, scaled by the % identity of the best structure, otherwise it is 0. Numeric, possible values: [0..6]

columns.label: Exp LIG
columns.description: Pocket Precedence component: Experimental ligand that satisfies rule-of-five. Score is 6 if the PDB ligands satisfy Lipinski's rule of five, scaled by the % identity of the best structure, otherwise it is 0. Numeric, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: Exp pocket raw
columns.description: Pocket precedence component: Fpocket score based on experimental structure. The score is based on the product of the maximum % identity of structures, the fraction of pocket residues inside a region and a score factor. The score factor depends on the maximum drug score calculated with FPocket on PDB structures, where 0 means no pockets with drug score > 0.5, otherwise 3 if drug score is > 0.5 and <= 0.7, otherwise 5 if drug score is > 0.7. Numeric, possible values: [0..5]

columns.label: CYS Exp LIG raw
columns.description: Cys precedence component: CYS near experimental ligand. If no PDB ligands or no solvent exposed Cys residue within 8A of any ligand atom, score is 0. If there are any number of cys residues within 8A and there is any number of ligands in PDB that satisfy the rule of 5, score is 6. To satisfy rule of 5 the ligand must get score higher or equal to 5 (from a max of 6).The score is then scaled by the %id of the top structure (chosen using BLAST score). Float, possible values: [0..6]

columns.label: CYS Exp pocket raw

The score is then scaled by the %id of the top structure (chosen using BLAST score). Float, possible values: [0..5]

columns.label: CYS AF2 pocket raw

If there are any number of cys residues within 8A of any number of pockets with drug score between 0.5 and 0.7, score is 2.The score is multiplied by mean of aa confidence values for corresponding residues. Float, possible values: [0..4]

columns.label: CYS AF2 pocket

columns.label: TCRD Level
columns.description: Tclin - These targets have activities in DrugCentral (ie. approved drugs) with known mechanism of action. Tchem - These targets have activities in ChEMBL, Guide to Pharmacology or DrugCentral that satisfy the activity thresholds. Tbio - These targets do not have known drug or small molecule activities that satisfy the activity thresholds AND satisfy one or more of the following criteria: 1. target is above the cutoff criteria for Tdark; 2. target is annotated with a Gene Ontology Molecular Function or Biological Process leaf term(s) with an Experimental Evidence code. Tdark - These are targets about which virtually nothing is known.

columns.label: CYS pLDDT confidence
columns.description: AlphaFold2 model confidence metric for the solvent-accessible CYS residues within the distance of 8A from any of the pocket residue atoms. Ordering corresponds to the `Region cysteines` column

columns.label: Region cysteines
columns.description: Cysteines identified within the distance of 8A from any of the pocket residue atoms and their SASA values

columns.label: Integrated Cov Druggability
columns.description: Max sum of HS SM Covalent and CYS Precedence scores calculated at a residue level. Float, possible values: [0..10]

columns.label: CYS AF2 pocket residue score
columns.description: Cys precedence component: CYS near AF2 pocket. If pocket drug score is less or equal to 0.5 the score is 0. If the cys residue is within 8A of any number of pockets with drug score greater than 0.7, score is 4. If the cys residue is within 8A of any number of pockets with drug score between 0.5 and 0.7, score is 2.The score is multiplied by mean of aa confidence values for corresponding residue. Float, possible values: [0..4]

columns.label: CYS PRECEDENCE residue score
columns.description: CYS pocket precedence: max value of the cys pocket prediction scores. Score is equal to the max of (Cys Exp LIG, Cys Exp Pocket and Cys AF2 Pocket) and is calculated on a residue level. Float, possible values: [0..6]
